41bool IsBundledButNotFirstMid(
42 const std::map<std::string, cricket::ContentGroup*>& bundle_groups_by_mid,
43 const std::string& mid) {
44 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(mid);
45 if (it == bundle_groups_by_mid.end())
46 return false;
47 return mid != *it->second->FirstContentName();
48}

52JsepTransportController::JsepTransportController(
53 rtc::Thread* network_thread,
54 cricket::PortAllocator* port_allocator,
55 AsyncDnsResolverFactoryInterface* async_dns_resolver_factory,
56 Config config)
57 : network_thread_(network_thread),
58 port_allocator_(port_allocator),
59 async_dns_resolver_factory_(async_dns_resolver_factory),
60 config_(config),
61 active_reset_srtp_params_(config.active_reset_srtp_params) {
62 // The |transport_observer| is assumed to be non-null.
63 RTC_DCHECK(config_.transport_observer);
64 RTC_DCHECK(config_.rtcp_handler);
65 RTC_DCHECK(config_.ice_transport_factory);
66 RTC_DCHECK(config_.on_dtls_handshake_error_);
67}
68
69JsepTransportController::~JsepTransportController() {
70 // Channel destructors may try to send packets, so this needs to happen on
71 // the network thread.
72 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
73 DestroyAllJsepTransports_n();
74}
75
76RTCError JsepTransportController::SetLocalDescription(
77 SdpType type,
78 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
79 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
80 return network_thread_->Invoke<RTCError>(
81 RTC_FROM_HERE, [=] { return SetLocalDescription(type, description); });
82 }
83
84 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
85 if (!initial_offerer_.has_value()) {
86 initial_offerer_.emplace(type == SdpType::kOffer);
87 if (*initial_offerer_) {
88 SetIceRole_n(cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING);
89 } else {
90 SetIceRole_n(cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED);
91 }
92 }
93 return ApplyDescription_n(/*local=*/true, type, description);
94}
95
96RTCError JsepTransportController::SetRemoteDescription(
97 SdpType type,
98 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
99 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
100 return network_thread_->Invoke<RTCError>(
101 RTC_FROM_HERE, [=] { return SetRemoteDescription(type, description); });
102 }
103
104 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
105 return ApplyDescription_n(/*local=*/false, type, description);
106}

183bool JsepTransportController::NeedsIceRestart(
184 const std::string& transport_name) const {
185 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
186
187 const cricket::JsepTransport* transport =
188 GetJsepTransportByName(transport_name);
189 if (!transport) {
190 return false;
191 }
192 return transport->needs_ice_restart();
193}

195absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole> JsepTransportController::GetDtlsRole(
196 const std::string& mid) const {
197 // TODO(tommi): Remove this hop. Currently it's called from the signaling
198 // thread during negotiations, potentially multiple times.
199 // WebRtcSessionDescriptionFactory::InternalCreateAnswer is one example.
200 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
201 return network_thread_->Invoke<absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole>>(
202 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] { return GetDtlsRole(mid); });
203 }
204
205 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
206
207 const cricket::JsepTransport* t = GetJsepTransportForMid(mid);
208 if (!t) {
209 return absl::optional<rtc::SSLRole>();
210 }
211 return t->GetDtlsRole();
212}

214bool JsepTransportController::SetLocalCertificate(
215 const rtc::scoped_refptr<rtc::RTCCertificate>& certificate) {
216 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
217 return network_thread_->Invoke<bool>(
218 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] { return SetLocalCertificate(certificate); });
219 }
220
221 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
222
223 // Can't change a certificate, or set a null certificate.
224 if (certificate_ || !certificate) {
225 return false;
226 }
227 certificate_ = certificate;
228
229 // Set certificate for JsepTransport, which verifies it matches the
230 // fingerprint in SDP, and DTLS transport.
231 // Fallback from DTLS to SDES is not supported.
232 for (auto& kv : jsep_transports_by_name_) {
233 kv.second->SetLocalCertificate(certificate_);
234 }
235 for (auto& dtls : GetDtlsTransports()) {
236 bool set_cert_success = dtls->SetLocalCertificate(certificate_);
237 RTC_DCHECK(set_cert_success);
238 }
239 return true;
240}

243JsepTransportController::GetLocalCertificate(
244 const std::string& transport_name) const {
245 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);

247 const cricket::JsepTransport* t = GetJsepTransportByName(transport_name);
248 if (!t) {
249 return nullptr;

251 return t->GetLocalCertificate();

254std::unique_ptr<rtc::SSLCertChain>
255JsepTransportController::GetRemoteSSLCertChain(
256 const std::string& transport_name) const {
257 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
258
259 // Get the certificate from the RTP transport's DTLS handshake. Should be
260 // identical to the RTCP transport's, since they were given the same remote
261 // fingerprint.
262 auto jsep_transport = GetJsepTransportByName(transport_name);
263 if (!jsep_transport) {
264 return nullptr;
265 }
266 auto dtls = jsep_transport->rtp_dtls_transport();
267 if (!dtls) {
268 return nullptr;
269 }
270
271 return dtls->GetRemoteSSLCertChain();
272}

286RTCError JsepTransportController::AddRemoteCandidates(
287 const std::string& transport_name,
288 const cricket::Candidates& candidates) {
289 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
290 RTC_DCHECK(VerifyCandidates(candidates).ok());
291 auto jsep_transport = GetJsepTransportByName(transport_name);
292 if (!jsep_transport) {
293 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Not adding candidate because the JsepTransport "
294 "doesn't exist. Ignore it.";
295 return RTCError::OK();
296 }
297 return jsep_transport->AddRemoteCandidates(candidates);
298}
299
300RTCError JsepTransportController::RemoveRemoteCandidates(
301 const cricket::Candidates& candidates) {
302 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
303 return network_thread_->Invoke<RTCError>(
304 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] { return RemoveRemoteCandidates(candidates); });
305 }
306
307 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
308
309 // Verify each candidate before passing down to the transport layer.
310 RTCError error = VerifyCandidates(candidates);
311 if (!error.ok()) {
312 return error;
313 }
314
315 std::map<std::string, cricket::Candidates> candidates_by_transport_name;
316 for (const cricket::Candidate& cand : candidates) {
317 if (!cand.transport_name().empty()) {
318 candidates_by_transport_name[cand.transport_name()].push_back(cand);
319 } else {
320 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Not removing candidate because it does not have a "
321 "transport name set: "
322 << cand.ToSensitiveString();
323 }
324 }
325
326 for (const auto& kv : candidates_by_transport_name) {
327 const std::string& transport_name = kv.first;
328 const cricket::Candidates& candidates = kv.second;
329 cricket::JsepTransport* jsep_transport =
330 GetJsepTransportByName(transport_name);
331 if (!jsep_transport) {
332 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
333 << "Not removing candidate because the JsepTransport doesn't exist.";
334 continue;
335 }
336 for (const cricket::Candidate& candidate : candidates) {
337 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* dtls =
338 candidate.component() == cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP
339 ? jsep_transport->rtp_dtls_transport()
340 : jsep_transport->rtcp_dtls_transport();
341 if (dtls) {
342 dtls->ice_transport()->RemoveRemoteCandidate(candidate);
343 }
344 }
345 }
346 return RTCError::OK();
347}

360void JsepTransportController::SetActiveResetSrtpParams(
361 bool active_reset_srtp_params) {
362 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
363 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [=] {
364 SetActiveResetSrtpParams(active_reset_srtp_params);
365 });
366 return;
367 }
368 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
369 RTC_LOG(INFO)
370 << "Updating the active_reset_srtp_params for JsepTransportController: "
371 << active_reset_srtp_params;
372 active_reset_srtp_params_ = active_reset_srtp_params;
373 for (auto& kv : jsep_transports_by_name_) {
374 kv.second->SetActiveResetSrtpParams(active_reset_srtp_params);
375 }
376}
377
378void JsepTransportController::RollbackTransports() {
379 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
380 network_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [=] { RollbackTransports(); });
381 return;
382 }
383 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
384 for (auto&& mid : pending_mids_) {
385 RemoveTransportForMid(mid);
386 }
387 for (auto&& mid : pending_mids_) {
388 MaybeDestroyJsepTransport(mid);
389 }
390 pending_mids_.clear();
391}

393rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::IceTransportInterface>
394JsepTransportController::CreateIceTransport(const std::string& transport_name,
395 bool rtcp) {
396 int component = rtcp ? cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTCP
397 : cricket::ICE_CANDIDATE_COMPONENT_RTP;
398
399 IceTransportInit init;
400 init.set_port_allocator(port_allocator_);
401 init.set_async_dns_resolver_factory(async_dns_resolver_factory_);
402 init.set_event_log(config_.event_log);
403 return config_.ice_transport_factory->CreateIceTransport(
404 transport_name, component, std::move(init));
405}

407std::unique_ptr<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal>
408JsepTransportController::CreateDtlsTransport(
409 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info,
410 cricket::IceTransportInternal* ice) {
411 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
412
413 std::unique_ptr<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal> dtls;
414
415 if (config_.dtls_transport_factory) {
416 dtls = config_.dtls_transport_factory->CreateDtlsTransport(
417 ice, config_.crypto_options, config_.ssl_max_version);
418 } else {
419 dtls = std::make_unique<cricket::DtlsTransport>(ice, config_.crypto_options,
420 config_.event_log,
421 config_.ssl_max_version);
422 }
423
424 RTC_DCHECK(dtls);
425 dtls->ice_transport()->SetIceRole(ice_role_);
426 dtls->ice_transport()->SetIceTiebreaker(ice_tiebreaker_);
427 dtls->ice_transport()->SetIceConfig(ice_config_);
428 if (certificate_) {
429 bool set_cert_success = dtls->SetLocalCertificate(certificate_);
430 RTC_DCHECK(set_cert_success);
431 }
432
433 // Connect to signals offered by the DTLS and ICE transport.
434 dtls->SignalWritableState.connect(
435 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportWritableState_n);
436 dtls->SignalReceivingState.connect(
437 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportReceivingState_n);
438 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalGatheringState.connect(
439 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportGatheringState_n);
440 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalCandidateGathered.connect(
441 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportCandidateGathered_n);
442 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalCandidateError.connect(
443 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportCandidateError_n);
444 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalCandidatesRemoved.connect(
445 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportCandidatesRemoved_n);
446 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalRoleConflict.connect(
447 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportRoleConflict_n);
448 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalStateChanged.connect(
449 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportStateChanged_n);
450 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalIceTransportStateChanged.connect(
451 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportStateChanged_n);
452 dtls->ice_transport()->SignalCandidatePairChanged.connect(
453 this, &JsepTransportController::OnTransportCandidatePairChanged_n);
454
455 dtls->SubscribeDtlsHandshakeError(
456 [this](rtc::SSLHandshakeError error) { OnDtlsHandshakeError(error); });
457 return dtls;
458}

460std::unique_ptr<webrtc::RtpTransport>
461JsepTransportController::CreateUnencryptedRtpTransport(
462 const std::string& transport_name,
463 rtc::PacketTransportInternal* rtp_packet_transport,
464 rtc::PacketTransportInternal* rtcp_packet_transport) {
465 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
466 auto unencrypted_rtp_transport =
467 std::make_unique<RtpTransport>(rtcp_packet_transport == nullptr);
468 unencrypted_rtp_transport->SetRtpPacketTransport(rtp_packet_transport);
469 if (rtcp_packet_transport) {
470 unencrypted_rtp_transport->SetRtcpPacketTransport(rtcp_packet_transport);
471 }
472 return unencrypted_rtp_transport;
473}

475std::unique_ptr<webrtc::SrtpTransport>
476JsepTransportController::CreateSdesTransport(
477 const std::string& transport_name,
478 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* rtp_dtls_transport,
479 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* rtcp_dtls_transport) {
480 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
481 auto srtp_transport =
482 std::make_unique<webrtc::SrtpTransport>(rtcp_dtls_transport == nullptr);
483 RTC_DCHECK(rtp_dtls_transport);
484 srtp_transport->SetRtpPacketTransport(rtp_dtls_transport);
485 if (rtcp_dtls_transport) {
486 srtp_transport->SetRtcpPacketTransport(rtcp_dtls_transport);
487 }
488 if (config_.enable_external_auth) {
489 srtp_transport->EnableExternalAuth();
490 }
491 return srtp_transport;
492}
493
494std::unique_ptr<webrtc::DtlsSrtpTransport>
495JsepTransportController::CreateDtlsSrtpTransport(
496 const std::string& transport_name,
497 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* rtp_dtls_transport,
498 cricket::DtlsTransportInternal* rtcp_dtls_transport) {
499 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
500 auto dtls_srtp_transport = std::make_unique<webrtc::DtlsSrtpTransport>(
501 rtcp_dtls_transport == nullptr);
502 if (config_.enable_external_auth) {
503 dtls_srtp_transport->EnableExternalAuth();
504 }
505
506 dtls_srtp_transport->SetDtlsTransports(rtp_dtls_transport,
507 rtcp_dtls_transport);
508 dtls_srtp_transport->SetActiveResetSrtpParams(active_reset_srtp_params_);
509 // Capturing this in the callback because JsepTransportController will always
510 // outlive the DtlsSrtpTransport.
511 dtls_srtp_transport->SetOnDtlsStateChange([this]() {
512 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(this->network_thread_);
513 this->UpdateAggregateStates_n();
514 });
515 return dtls_srtp_transport;
516}
517
518std::vector<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal*>
519JsepTransportController::GetDtlsTransports() {
520 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
521 std::vector<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal*> dtls_transports;
522 for (auto it = jsep_transports_by_name_.begin();
523 it != jsep_transports_by_name_.end(); ++it) {
524 auto jsep_transport = it->second.get();
525 RTC_DCHECK(jsep_transport);
526 if (jsep_transport->rtp_dtls_transport()) {
527 dtls_transports.push_back(jsep_transport->rtp_dtls_transport());
528 }
529
530 if (jsep_transport->rtcp_dtls_transport()) {
531 dtls_transports.push_back(jsep_transport->rtcp_dtls_transport());
532 }
533 }
534 return dtls_transports;
535}
536
537RTCError JsepTransportController::ApplyDescription_n(
538 bool local,
539 SdpType type,
540 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
541 RTC_DCHECK(description);
542
543 if (local) {
544 local_desc_ = description;
545 } else {
546 remote_desc_ = description;
547 }
548
549 RTCError error;
550 error = ValidateAndMaybeUpdateBundleGroups(local, type, description);
551 if (!error.ok()) {
552 return error;
553 }
554 // Established BUNDLE groups by MID.
555 std::map<std::string, cricket::ContentGroup*>
556 established_bundle_groups_by_mid;
557 for (const auto& bundle_group : bundle_groups_) {
558 for (const std::string& content_name : bundle_group->content_names()) {
559 established_bundle_groups_by_mid[content_name] = bundle_group.get();
560 }
561 }
562
563 std::map<const cricket::ContentGroup*, std::vector<int>>
564 merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle;
565 if (!bundle_groups_.empty()) {
566 merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle =
567 MergeEncryptedHeaderExtensionIdsForBundles(
568 established_bundle_groups_by_mid, description);
569 }
570
571 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info : description->contents()) {
572 // Don't create transports for rejected m-lines and bundled m-lines.
573 if (content_info.rejected ||
574 IsBundledButNotFirstMid(established_bundle_groups_by_mid,
575 content_info.name)) {
576 continue;
577 }
578 error = MaybeCreateJsepTransport(local, content_info, *description);
579 if (!error.ok()) {
580 return error;
581 }
582 }
583
584 RTC_DCHECK(description->contents().size() ==
585 description->transport_infos().size());
586 for (size_t i = 0; i < description->contents().size(); ++i) {
587 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info = description->contents()[i];
588 const cricket::TransportInfo& transport_info =
589 description->transport_infos()[i];
590 if (content_info.rejected) {
591 // This may cause groups to be removed from |bundle_groups_| and
592 // |established_bundle_groups_by_mid|.
593 HandleRejectedContent(content_info, established_bundle_groups_by_mid);
594 continue;
595 }
596
597 auto it = established_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_info.name);
598 const cricket::ContentGroup* established_bundle_group =
599 it != established_bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
600
601 // For bundle members that are not BUNDLE-tagged (not first in the group),
602 // configure their transport to be the same as the BUNDLE-tagged transport.
603 if (established_bundle_group &&
604 content_info.name != *established_bundle_group->FirstContentName()) {
605 if (!HandleBundledContent(content_info, *established_bundle_group)) {
606 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
607 "Failed to process the bundled m= section with "
608 "mid='" +
609 content_info.name + "'.");
610 }
611 continue;
612 }
613
614 error = ValidateContent(content_info);
615 if (!error.ok()) {
616 return error;
617 }
618
619 std::vector<int> extension_ids;
620 // Is BUNDLE-tagged (first in the group)?
621 if (established_bundle_group &&
622 content_info.name == *established_bundle_group->FirstContentName()) {
623 auto it = merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle.find(
624 established_bundle_group);
625 RTC_DCHECK(it != merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle.end());
626 extension_ids = it->second;
627 } else {
628 extension_ids = GetEncryptedHeaderExtensionIds(content_info);
629 }
630
631 int rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id =
632 GetRtpAbsSendTimeHeaderExtensionId(content_info);
633
634 cricket::JsepTransport* transport =
635 GetJsepTransportForMid(content_info.name);
636 RTC_DCHECK(transport);
637
638 SetIceRole_n(DetermineIceRole(transport, transport_info, type, local));
639
640 cricket::JsepTransportDescription jsep_description =
641 CreateJsepTransportDescription(content_info, transport_info,
642 extension_ids, rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id);
643 if (local) {
644 error =
645 transport->SetLocalJsepTransportDescription(jsep_description, type);
646 } else {
647 error =
648 transport->SetRemoteJsepTransportDescription(jsep_description, type);
649 }
650
651 if (!error.ok()) {
652 LOG_AND_RETURN_ERROR(
653 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
654 "Failed to apply the description for m= section with mid='" +
655 content_info.name + "': " + error.message());
656 }
657 }
658 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
659 pending_mids_.clear();
660 }
661 return RTCError::OK();
662}
663
664RTCError JsepTransportController::ValidateAndMaybeUpdateBundleGroups(
665 bool local,
666 SdpType type,
667 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
668 RTC_DCHECK(description);
669
670 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> new_bundle_groups =
671 description->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
672 // Verify |new_bundle_groups|.
673 std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*> new_bundle_groups_by_mid;
674 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* new_bundle_group : new_bundle_groups) {
675 for (const std::string& content_name : new_bundle_group->content_names()) {
676 // The BUNDLE group must not contain a MID that is a member of a different
677 // BUNDLE group, or that contains the same MID multiple times.
678 if (new_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_name) !=
679 new_bundle_groups_by_mid.end()) {
680 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
681 "A BUNDLE group contains a MID='" + content_name +
682 "' that is already in a BUNDLE group.");
683 }
684 new_bundle_groups_by_mid.insert(
685 std::make_pair(content_name, new_bundle_group));
686 // The BUNDLE group must not contain a MID that no m= section has.
687 if (!description->GetContentByName(content_name)) {
688 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
689 "A BUNDLE group contains a MID='" + content_name +
690 "' matching no m= section.");
691 }
692 }
693 }
694
695 if (type == SdpType::kAnswer) {
696 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> offered_bundle_groups =
697 local ? remote_desc_->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE)
698 : local_desc_->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
699
700 std::map<std::string, const cricket::ContentGroup*>
701 offered_bundle_groups_by_mid;
702 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* offered_bundle_group :
703 offered_bundle_groups) {
704 for (const std::string& content_name :
705 offered_bundle_group->content_names()) {
706 offered_bundle_groups_by_mid[content_name] = offered_bundle_group;
707 }
708 }
709
710 std::map<const cricket::ContentGroup*, const cricket::ContentGroup*>
711 new_bundle_groups_by_offered_bundle_groups;
712 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* new_bundle_group : new_bundle_groups) {
713 if (!new_bundle_group->FirstContentName()) {
714 // Empty groups could be a subset of any group.
715 continue;
716 }
717 // The group in the answer (new_bundle_group) must have a corresponding
718 // group in the offer (original_group), because the answer groups may only
719 // be subsets of the offer groups.
720 auto it = offered_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(
721 *new_bundle_group->FirstContentName());
722 if (it == offered_bundle_groups_by_mid.end()) {
723 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
724 "A BUNDLE group was added in the answer that did not "
725 "exist in the offer.");
726 }
727 const cricket::ContentGroup* offered_bundle_group = it->second;
728 if (new_bundle_groups_by_offered_bundle_groups.find(
729 offered_bundle_group) !=
730 new_bundle_groups_by_offered_bundle_groups.end()) {
731 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
732 "A MID in the answer has changed group.");
733 }
734 new_bundle_groups_by_offered_bundle_groups.insert(
735 std::make_pair(offered_bundle_group, new_bundle_group));
736 for (const std::string& content_name :
737 new_bundle_group->content_names()) {
738 it = offered_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_name);
739 // The BUNDLE group in answer should be a subset of offered group.
740 if (it == offered_bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ||
741 it->second != offered_bundle_group) {
742 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
743 "A BUNDLE group in answer contains a MID='" +
744 content_name +
745 "' that was not in the offered group.");
746 }
747 }
748 }
749
750 for (const auto& bundle_group : bundle_groups_) {
751 for (const std::string& content_name : bundle_group->content_names()) {
752 // An answer that removes m= sections from pre-negotiated BUNDLE group
753 // without rejecting it, is invalid.
754 auto it = new_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_name);
755 if (it == new_bundle_groups_by_mid.end()) {
756 auto* content_info = description->GetContentByName(content_name);
757 if (!content_info || !content_info->rejected) {
758 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
759 "Answer cannot remove m= section with mid='" +
760 content_name +
761 "' from already-established BUNDLE group.");
762 }
763 }
764 }
765 }
766 }
767
768 if (config_.bundle_policy ==
769 PeerConnectionInterface::kBundlePolicyMaxBundle &&
770 !description->HasGroup(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE)) {
771 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
772 "max-bundle is used but no bundle group found.");
773 }
774
775 if (ShouldUpdateBundleGroup(type, description)) {
776 bundle_groups_.clear();
777 for (const cricket::ContentGroup* new_bundle_group : new_bundle_groups) {
778 bundle_groups_.push_back(
779 std::make_unique<cricket::ContentGroup>(*new_bundle_group));
780 }
781 }
782
783 for (const auto& bundle_group : bundle_groups_) {
784 if (!bundle_group->FirstContentName())
785 continue;
786
787 // The first MID in a BUNDLE group is BUNDLE-tagged.
788 auto bundled_content =
789 description->GetContentByName(*bundle_group->FirstContentName());
790 if (!bundled_content) {
791 return RTCError(
792 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
793 "An m= section associated with the BUNDLE-tag doesn't exist.");
794 }
795
796 // If the |bundled_content| is rejected, other contents in the bundle group
797 // must also be rejected.
798 if (bundled_content->rejected) {
799 for (const auto& content_name : bundle_group->content_names()) {
800 auto other_content = description->GetContentByName(content_name);
801 if (!other_content->rejected) {
802 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
803 "The m= section with mid='" + content_name +
804 "' should be rejected.");
805 }
806 }
807 }
808 }
809 return RTCError::OK();
810}
811
812RTCError JsepTransportController::ValidateContent(
813 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info) {
814 if (config_.rtcp_mux_policy ==
815 PeerConnectionInterface::kRtcpMuxPolicyRequire &&
816 content_info.type == cricket::MediaProtocolType::kRtp &&
817 !content_info.media_description()->rtcp_mux()) {
818 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
819 "The m= section with mid='" + content_info.name +
820 "' is invalid. RTCP-MUX is not "
821 "enabled when it is required.");
822 }
823 return RTCError::OK();
824}
825
826void JsepTransportController::HandleRejectedContent(
827 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info,
828 std::map<std::string, cricket::ContentGroup*>&
829 established_bundle_groups_by_mid) {
830 // If the content is rejected, let the
831 // BaseChannel/SctpTransport change the RtpTransport/DtlsTransport first,
832 // then destroy the cricket::JsepTransport.
833 auto it = established_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_info.name);
834 cricket::ContentGroup* bundle_group =
835 it != established_bundle_groups_by_mid.end() ? it->second : nullptr;
836 if (bundle_group && !bundle_group->content_names().empty() &&
837 content_info.name == *bundle_group->FirstContentName()) {
838 // Rejecting a BUNDLE group's first mid means we are rejecting the entire
839 // group.
840 for (const auto& content_name : bundle_group->content_names()) {
841 RemoveTransportForMid(content_name);
842 // We are about to delete this BUNDLE group, erase all mappings to it.
843 it = established_bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_name);
844 RTC_DCHECK(it != established_bundle_groups_by_mid.end());
845 established_bundle_groups_by_mid.erase(it);
846 }
847 // Delete the BUNDLE group.
848 auto bundle_group_it = std::find_if(
849 bundle_groups_.begin(), bundle_groups_.end(),
850 [bundle_group](std::unique_ptr<cricket::ContentGroup>& group) {
851 return bundle_group == group.get();
852 });
853 RTC_DCHECK(bundle_group_it != bundle_groups_.end());
854 bundle_groups_.erase(bundle_group_it);
855 } else {
856 RemoveTransportForMid(content_info.name);
857 if (bundle_group) {
858 // Remove the rejected content from the |bundle_group|.
859 bundle_group->RemoveContentName(content_info.name);
860 }
861 }
862 MaybeDestroyJsepTransport(content_info.name);
863}
864
865bool JsepTransportController::HandleBundledContent(
866 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info,
867 const cricket::ContentGroup& bundle_group) {
868 RTC_DCHECK(bundle_group.FirstContentName());
869 auto jsep_transport =
870 GetJsepTransportByName(*bundle_group.FirstContentName());
871 RTC_DCHECK(jsep_transport);
872 // If the content is bundled, let the
873 // BaseChannel/SctpTransport change the RtpTransport/DtlsTransport first,
874 // then destroy the cricket::JsepTransport.
875 if (SetTransportForMid(content_info.name, jsep_transport)) {
876 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9719) For media transport this is far from ideal,
877 // because it means that we first create media transport and start
878 // connecting it, and then we destroy it. We will need to address it before
879 // video path is enabled.
880 MaybeDestroyJsepTransport(content_info.name);
881 return true;
882 }
883 return false;
884}
885
886bool JsepTransportController::SetTransportForMid(
887 const std::string& mid,
888 cricket::JsepTransport* jsep_transport) {
889 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
890 RTC_DCHECK(jsep_transport);
891
892 auto it = mid_to_transport_.find(mid);
893 if (it != mid_to_transport_.end() && it->second == jsep_transport)
894 return true;
895
896 pending_mids_.push_back(mid);
897
898 if (it == mid_to_transport_.end()) {
899 mid_to_transport_.insert(std::make_pair(mid, jsep_transport));
900 } else {
901 it->second = jsep_transport;
902 }
903
904 return config_.transport_observer->OnTransportChanged(
905 mid, jsep_transport->rtp_transport(), jsep_transport->RtpDtlsTransport(),
906 jsep_transport->data_channel_transport());
907}
908
909void JsepTransportController::RemoveTransportForMid(const std::string& mid) {
910 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
911 bool ret = config_.transport_observer->OnTransportChanged(mid, nullptr,
912 nullptr, nullptr);
913 // Calling OnTransportChanged with nullptr should always succeed, since it is
914 // only expected to fail when adding media to a transport (not removing).
915 RTC_DCHECK(ret);
916
917 mid_to_transport_.erase(mid);
918}

920cricket::JsepTransportDescription
921JsepTransportController::CreateJsepTransportDescription(
922 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info,
923 const cricket::TransportInfo& transport_info,
924 const std::vector<int>& encrypted_extension_ids,
925 int rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id) {
926 const cricket::MediaContentDescription* content_desc =
927 content_info.media_description();
928 RTC_DCHECK(content_desc);
929 bool rtcp_mux_enabled = content_info.type == cricket::MediaProtocolType::kSctp
930 ? true
931 : content_desc->rtcp_mux();
932
933 return cricket::JsepTransportDescription(
934 rtcp_mux_enabled, content_desc->cryptos(), encrypted_extension_ids,
935 rtp_abs_sendtime_extn_id, transport_info.description);
936}
937
938bool JsepTransportController::ShouldUpdateBundleGroup(
939 SdpType type,
940 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
941 if (config_.bundle_policy ==
942 PeerConnectionInterface::kBundlePolicyMaxBundle) {
943 return true;
944 }
945
946 if (type != SdpType::kAnswer) {
947 return false;
948 }
949
950 RTC_DCHECK(local_desc_ && remote_desc_);
951 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> local_bundles =
952 local_desc_->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
953 std::vector<const cricket::ContentGroup*> remote_bundles =
954 remote_desc_->GetGroupsByName(cricket::GROUP_TYPE_BUNDLE);
955 return !local_bundles.empty() && !remote_bundles.empty();
956}
957
958std::vector<int> JsepTransportController::GetEncryptedHeaderExtensionIds(
959 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info) {
960 const cricket::MediaContentDescription* content_desc =
961 content_info.media_description();
962
963 if (!config_.crypto_options.srtp.enable_encrypted_rtp_header_extensions) {
964 return std::vector<int>();
965 }
966
967 std::vector<int> encrypted_header_extension_ids;
968 for (const auto& extension : content_desc->rtp_header_extensions()) {
969 if (!extension.encrypt) {
970 continue;
971 }
972 if (!absl::c_linear_search(encrypted_header_extension_ids, extension.id)) {
973 encrypted_header_extension_ids.push_back(extension.id);
974 }
975 }
976 return encrypted_header_extension_ids;
977}
978
979std::map<const cricket::ContentGroup*, std::vector<int>>
980JsepTransportController::MergeEncryptedHeaderExtensionIdsForBundles(
981 const std::map<std::string, cricket::ContentGroup*>& bundle_groups_by_mid,
982 const cricket::SessionDescription* description) {
983 RTC_DCHECK(description);
984 RTC_DCHECK(!bundle_groups_.empty());
985 std::map<const cricket::ContentGroup*, std::vector<int>>
986 merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle;
987 // Union the encrypted header IDs in the group when bundle is enabled.
988 for (const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info : description->contents()) {
989 auto it = bundle_groups_by_mid.find(content_info.name);
990 if (it == bundle_groups_by_mid.end())
991 continue;
992 // Get or create list of IDs for the BUNDLE group.
993 std::vector<int>& merged_ids =
994 merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle[it->second];
995 // Add IDs not already in the list.
996 std::vector<int> extension_ids =
997 GetEncryptedHeaderExtensionIds(content_info);
998 for (int id : extension_ids) {
999 if (!absl::c_linear_search(merged_ids, id)) {
1000 merged_ids.push_back(id);
1001 }
1002 }
1003 }
1004 return merged_encrypted_extension_ids_by_bundle;
1005}
1006
1007int JsepTransportController::GetRtpAbsSendTimeHeaderExtensionId(
1008 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info) {
1009 if (!config_.enable_external_auth) {
1010 return -1;
1011 }
1012
1013 const cricket::MediaContentDescription* content_desc =
1014 content_info.media_description();
1015
1016 const webrtc::RtpExtension* send_time_extension =
1017 webrtc::RtpExtension::FindHeaderExtensionByUri(
1018 content_desc->rtp_header_extensions(),
1019 webrtc::RtpExtension::kAbsSendTimeUri);
1020 return send_time_extension ? send_time_extension->id : -1;
1021}

1046
1047RTCError JsepTransportController::MaybeCreateJsepTransport(
1048 bool local,
1049 const cricket::ContentInfo& content_info,
1050 const cricket::SessionDescription& description) {
1051 cricket::JsepTransport* transport = GetJsepTransportByName(content_info.name);
1052 if (transport) {
1053 return RTCError::OK();
1054 }
1055
1056 const cricket::MediaContentDescription* content_desc =
1057 content_info.media_description();
1058 if (certificate_ && !content_desc->cryptos().empty()) {
1059 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
1060 "SDES and DTLS-SRTP cannot be enabled at the same time.");
1061 }
1062
1063 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::IceTransportInterface> ice =
1064 CreateIceTransport(content_info.name, /*rtcp=*/false);
1065 RTC_DCHECK(ice);
1066
1067 std::unique_ptr<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal> rtp_dtls_transport =
1068 CreateDtlsTransport(content_info, ice->internal());
1069
1070 std::unique_ptr<cricket::DtlsTransportInternal> rtcp_dtls_transport;
1071 std::unique_ptr<RtpTransport> unencrypted_rtp_transport;
1072 std::unique_ptr<SrtpTransport> sdes_transport;
1073 std::unique_ptr<DtlsSrtpTransport> dtls_srtp_transport;
1074
1075 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::IceTransportInterface> rtcp_ice;
1076 if (config_.rtcp_mux_policy !=
1077 PeerConnectionInterface::kRtcpMuxPolicyRequire &&
1078 content_info.type == cricket::MediaProtocolType::kRtp) {
1079 rtcp_ice = CreateIceTransport(content_info.name, /*rtcp=*/true);
1080 rtcp_dtls_transport =
1081 CreateDtlsTransport(content_info, rtcp_ice->internal());
1082 }
1083
1084 if (config_.disable_encryption) {
1085 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1086 << "Creating UnencryptedRtpTransport, becayse encryption is disabled.";
1087 unencrypted_rtp_transport = CreateUnencryptedRtpTransport(
1088 content_info.name, rtp_dtls_transport.get(), rtcp_dtls_transport.get());
1089 } else if (!content_desc->cryptos().empty()) {
1090 sdes_transport = CreateSdesTransport(
1091 content_info.name, rtp_dtls_transport.get(), rtcp_dtls_transport.get());
1092 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating SdesTransport.";
1093 } else {
1094 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Creating DtlsSrtpTransport.";
1095 dtls_srtp_transport = CreateDtlsSrtpTransport(
1096 content_info.name, rtp_dtls_transport.get(), rtcp_dtls_transport.get());
1097 }
1098
1099 std::unique_ptr<cricket::SctpTransportInternal> sctp_transport;
1100 if (config_.sctp_factory) {
1101 sctp_transport =
1102 config_.sctp_factory->CreateSctpTransport(rtp_dtls_transport.get());
1103 }
1104
1105 std::unique_ptr<cricket::JsepTransport> jsep_transport =
1106 std::make_unique<cricket::JsepTransport>(
1107 content_info.name, certificate_, std::move(ice), std::move(rtcp_ice),
1108 std::move(unencrypted_rtp_transport), std::move(sdes_transport),
1109 std::move(dtls_srtp_transport), std::move(rtp_dtls_transport),
1110 std::move(rtcp_dtls_transport), std::move(sctp_transport));
1111
1112 jsep_transport->rtp_transport()->SignalRtcpPacketReceived.connect(
1113 this, &JsepTransportController::OnRtcpPacketReceived_n);
1114
1115 jsep_transport->SignalRtcpMuxActive.connect(
1116 this, &JsepTransportController::UpdateAggregateStates_n);
1117 SetTransportForMid(content_info.name, jsep_transport.get());
1118
1119 jsep_transports_by_name_[content_info.name] = std::move(jsep_transport);
1120 UpdateAggregateStates_n();
1121 return RTCError::OK();
1122}
1123
1124void JsepTransportController::MaybeDestroyJsepTransport(
1125 const std::string& mid) {
1126 auto jsep_transport = GetJsepTransportByName(mid);
1127 if (!jsep_transport) {
1128 return;
1129 }
1130
1131 // Don't destroy the JsepTransport if there are still media sections referring
1132 // to it.
1133 for (const auto& kv : mid_to_transport_) {
1134 if (kv.second == jsep_transport) {
1135 return;
1136 }
1137 }
1138
1139 jsep_transports_by_name_.erase(mid);
1140 UpdateAggregateStates_n();
1141}
1142
1143void JsepTransportController::DestroyAllJsepTransports_n() {
1144 for (const auto& jsep_transport : jsep_transports_by_name_) {
1145 config_.transport_observer->OnTransportChanged(jsep_transport.first,
1146 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr);
1147 }
1148
1149 jsep_transports_by_name_.clear();
1150}
1151
1152void JsepTransportController::SetIceRole_n(cricket::IceRole ice_role) {
1153 ice_role_ = ice_role;
1154 auto dtls_transports = GetDtlsTransports();
1155 for (auto& dtls : dtls_transports) {
1156 dtls->ice_transport()->SetIceRole(ice_role_);
1157 }
1158}
1159
1160cricket::IceRole JsepTransportController::DetermineIceRole(
1161 cricket::JsepTransport* jsep_transport,
1162 const cricket::TransportInfo& transport_info,
1163 SdpType type,
1164 bool local) {
1165 cricket::IceRole ice_role = ice_role_;
1166 auto tdesc = transport_info.description;
1167 if (local) {
1168 // The initial offer side may use ICE Lite, in which case, per RFC5245
1169 // Section 5.1.1, the answer side should take the controlling role if it is
1170 // in the full ICE mode.
1171 //
1172 // When both sides use ICE Lite, the initial offer side must take the
1173 // controlling role, and this is the default logic implemented in
1174 // SetLocalDescription in JsepTransportController.
1175 if (jsep_transport->remote_description() &&
1176 jsep_transport->remote_description()->transport_desc.ice_mode ==
1177 cricket::ICEMODE_LITE &&
1178 ice_role_ == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED &&
1179 tdesc.ice_mode == cricket::ICEMODE_FULL) {
1180 ice_role = cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING;
1181 }
1182 } else {
1183 // If our role is cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED and the remote endpoint
1184 // supports only ice_lite, this local endpoint should take the CONTROLLING
1185 // role.
1186 // TODO(deadbeef): This is a session-level attribute, so it really shouldn't
1187 // be in a TransportDescription in the first place...
1188 if (ice_role_ == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED &&
1189 tdesc.ice_mode == cricket::ICEMODE_LITE) {
1190 ice_role = cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING;
1191 }
1192
1193 // If we use ICE Lite and the remote endpoint uses the full implementation
1194 // of ICE, the local endpoint must take the controlled role, and the other
1195 // side must be the controlling role.
1196 if (jsep_transport->local_description() &&
1197 jsep_transport->local_description()->transport_desc.ice_mode ==
1198 cricket::ICEMODE_LITE &&
1199 ice_role_ == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING &&
1200 tdesc.ice_mode == cricket::ICEMODE_FULL) {
1201 ice_role = cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED;
1202 }
1203 }
1204
1205 return ice_role;
1206}

1253
1254void JsepTransportController::OnTransportRoleConflict_n(
1255 cricket::IceTransportInternal* transport) {
1256 // Note: since the role conflict is handled entirely on the network thread,
1257 // we don't need to worry about role conflicts occurring on two ports at
1258 // once. The first one encountered should immediately reverse the role.
1259 cricket::IceRole reversed_role = (ice_role_ == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING)
1260 ? cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLED
1261 : cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING;
1262 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Got role conflict; switching to "
1263 << (reversed_role == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING
1264 ? "controlling"
1265 : "controlled")
1266 << " role.";
1267 SetIceRole_n(reversed_role);
1268}
1269
1270void JsepTransportController::OnTransportStateChanged_n(
1271 cricket::IceTransportInternal* transport) {
1272 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << transport->transport_name() << " Transport "
1273 << transport->component()
1274 << " state changed. Check if state is complete.";
1275 UpdateAggregateStates_n();
1276}
1277
1278void JsepTransportController::UpdateAggregateStates_n() {
1279 auto dtls_transports = GetDtlsTransports();
1280 cricket::IceConnectionState new_connection_state =
1281 cricket::kIceConnectionConnecting;
1282 PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState new_ice_connection_state =
1283 PeerConnectionInterface::IceConnectionState::kIceConnectionNew;
1284 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState new_combined_state =
1285 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kNew;
1286 cricket::IceGatheringState new_gathering_state = cricket::kIceGatheringNew;
1287 bool any_failed = false;
1288 bool all_connected = !dtls_transports.empty();
1289 bool all_completed = !dtls_transports.empty();
1290 bool any_gathering = false;
1291 bool all_done_gathering = !dtls_transports.empty();
1292
1293 std::map<IceTransportState, int> ice_state_counts;
1294 std::map<cricket::DtlsTransportState, int> dtls_state_counts;
1295
1296 for (const auto& dtls : dtls_transports) {
1297 any_failed = any_failed || dtls->ice_transport()->GetState() ==
1298 cricket::IceTransportState::STATE_FAILED;
1299 all_connected = all_connected && dtls->writable();
1300 all_completed =
1301 all_completed && dtls->writable() &&
1302 dtls->ice_transport()->GetState() ==
1303 cricket::IceTransportState::STATE_COMPLETED &&
1304 dtls->ice_transport()->GetIceRole() == cricket::ICEROLE_CONTROLLING &&
1305 dtls->ice_transport()->gathering_state() ==
1306 cricket::kIceGatheringComplete;
1307 any_gathering = any_gathering || dtls->ice_transport()->gathering_state() !=
1308 cricket::kIceGatheringNew;
1309 all_done_gathering =
1310 all_done_gathering && dtls->ice_transport()->gathering_state() ==
1311 cricket::kIceGatheringComplete;
1312
1313 dtls_state_counts[dtls->dtls_state()]++;
1314 ice_state_counts[dtls->ice_transport()->GetIceTransportState()]++;
1315 }
1316
1317 if (any_failed) {
1318 new_connection_state = cricket::kIceConnectionFailed;
1319 } else if (all_completed) {
1320 new_connection_state = cricket::kIceConnectionCompleted;
1321 } else if (all_connected) {
1322 new_connection_state = cricket::kIceConnectionConnected;
1323 }
1324 if (ice_connection_state_ != new_connection_state) {
1325 ice_connection_state_ = new_connection_state;
1326
1327 signal_ice_connection_state_.Send(new_connection_state);
1328 }
1329
1330 // Compute the current RTCIceConnectionState as described in
1331 // https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#dom-rtciceconnectionstate.
1332 // The PeerConnection is responsible for handling the "closed" state.
1333 int total_ice_checking = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kChecking];
1334 int total_ice_connected = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kConnected];
1335 int total_ice_completed = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kCompleted];
1336 int total_ice_failed = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kFailed];
1337 int total_ice_disconnected =
1338 ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kDisconnected];
1339 int total_ice_closed = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kClosed];
1340 int total_ice_new = ice_state_counts[IceTransportState::kNew];
1341 int total_ice = dtls_transports.size();
1342
1343 if (total_ice_failed > 0) {
1344 // Any RTCIceTransports are in the "failed" state.
1345 new_ice_connection_state = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionFailed;
1346 } else if (total_ice_disconnected > 0) {
1347 // None of the previous states apply and any RTCIceTransports are in the
1348 // "disconnected" state.
1349 new_ice_connection_state =
1350 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionDisconnected;
1351 } else if (total_ice_new + total_ice_closed == total_ice) {
1352 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports are in the
1353 // "new" or "closed" state, or there are no transports.
1354 new_ice_connection_state = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionNew;
1355 } else if (total_ice_new + total_ice_checking > 0) {
1356 // None of the previous states apply and any RTCIceTransports are in the
1357 // "new" or "checking" state.
1358 new_ice_connection_state = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionChecking;
1359 } else if (total_ice_completed + total_ice_closed == total_ice ||
1360 all_completed) {
1361 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports are in the
1362 // "completed" or "closed" state.
1363 //
1364 // TODO(https://bugs.webrtc.org/10356): The all_completed condition is added
1365 // to mimic the behavior of the old ICE connection state, and should be
1366 // removed once we get end-of-candidates signaling in place.
1367 new_ice_connection_state = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionCompleted;
1368 } else if (total_ice_connected + total_ice_completed + total_ice_closed ==
1369 total_ice) {
1370 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports are in the
1371 // "connected", "completed" or "closed" state.
1372 new_ice_connection_state = PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected;
1373 } else {
1374 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1375 }
1376
1377 if (standardized_ice_connection_state_ != new_ice_connection_state) {
1378 if (standardized_ice_connection_state_ ==
1379 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionChecking &&
1380 new_ice_connection_state ==
1381 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionCompleted) {
1382 // Ensure that we never skip over the "connected" state.
1383 signal_standardized_ice_connection_state_.Send(
1384 PeerConnectionInterface::kIceConnectionConnected);
1385 }
1386 standardized_ice_connection_state_ = new_ice_connection_state;
1387 signal_standardized_ice_connection_state_.Send(new_ice_connection_state);
1388 }
1389
1390 // Compute the current RTCPeerConnectionState as described in
1391 // https://www.w3.org/TR/webrtc/#dom-rtcpeerconnectionstate.
1392 // The PeerConnection is responsible for handling the "closed" state.
1393 // Note that "connecting" is only a valid state for DTLS transports while
1394 // "checking", "completed" and "disconnected" are only valid for ICE
1395 // transports.
1396 int total_connected = total_ice_connected +
1397 dtls_state_counts[cricket::DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTED];
1398 int total_dtls_connecting =
1399 dtls_state_counts[cricket::DTLS_TRANSPORT_CONNECTING];
1400 int total_failed =
1401 total_ice_failed + dtls_state_counts[cricket::DTLS_TRANSPORT_FAILED];
1402 int total_closed =
1403 total_ice_closed + dtls_state_counts[cricket::DTLS_TRANSPORT_CLOSED];
1404 int total_new =
1405 total_ice_new + dtls_state_counts[cricket::DTLS_TRANSPORT_NEW];
1406 int total_transports = total_ice * 2;
1407
1408 if (total_failed > 0) {
1409 // Any of the RTCIceTransports or RTCDtlsTransports are in a "failed" state.
1410 new_combined_state = PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kFailed;
1411 } else if (total_ice_disconnected > 0) {
1412 // None of the previous states apply and any RTCIceTransports or
1413 // RTCDtlsTransports are in the "disconnected" state.
1414 new_combined_state =
1415 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kDisconnected;
1416 } else if (total_new + total_closed == total_transports) {
1417 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports and
1418 // RTCDtlsTransports are in the "new" or "closed" state, or there are no
1419 // transports.
1420 new_combined_state = PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kNew;
1421 } else if (total_new + total_dtls_connecting + total_ice_checking > 0) {
1422 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports or
1423 // RTCDtlsTransports are in the "new", "connecting" or "checking" state.
1424 new_combined_state =
1425 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kConnecting;
1426 } else if (total_connected + total_ice_completed + total_closed ==
1427 total_transports) {
1428 // None of the previous states apply and all RTCIceTransports and
1429 // RTCDtlsTransports are in the "connected", "completed" or "closed" state.
1430 new_combined_state =
1431 PeerConnectionInterface::PeerConnectionState::kConnected;
1432 } else {
1433 RTC_NOTREACHED();
1434 }
1435
1436 if (combined_connection_state_ != new_combined_state) {
1437 combined_connection_state_ = new_combined_state;
1438 signal_connection_state_.Send(new_combined_state);
1439 }
1440
1441 // Compute the gathering state.
1442 if (dtls_transports.empty()) {
1443 new_gathering_state = cricket::kIceGatheringNew;
1444 } else if (all_done_gathering) {
1445 new_gathering_state = cricket::kIceGatheringComplete;
1446 } else if (any_gathering) {
1447 new_gathering_state = cricket::kIceGatheringGathering;
1448 }
1449 if (ice_gathering_state_ != new_gathering_state) {
1450 ice_gathering_state_ = new_gathering_state;
1451 signal_ice_gathering_state_.Send(new_gathering_state);
1452 }
1453}

1455void JsepTransportController::OnRtcpPacketReceived_n(
1456 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
1457 int64_t packet_time_us) {
1458 RTC_DCHECK(config_.rtcp_handler);
1459 config_.rtcp_handler(*packet, packet_time_us);
1460}
